altigaSepStatsMibModule.name: altigaSepStatsMibModule

revisions.description: Added new enum value to alSepModuleStatsType and alSepModuleStatsState.

altigaSepStatsMibModule.contactinfo: Cisco Systems 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-cvpn3000@cisco.com
altigaSepStatsMibModule.description: The Cisco VPN 3000 Series SEP Statistics MIB models counters and objects that are of management interest for the SEP hardware. Acronyms The following acronyms are used in this document: MIB: Management Information Base RSA: Rivest, Shamir, and Adelman SEP: Scalable Encryption Processor

alSepModuleStatsSlotNum.name: alSepModuleStatsSlotNum
alSepModuleStatsSlotNum.description: The physical slot this SEP is connected to.

alSepModuleStatsType.name: alSepModuleStatsType
alSepModuleStatsType.description: Indicates the type of HW engine used to perform the cryptographic transforms. cryptSet: First generation of Hardware Cryptographic Processor. cryptIc: Cryptographic Integrated Circuit. bcm582x: BroadCom 582x series Hardware Cryptographic Products.

alSepModuleStatsState.name: alSepModuleStatsState
alSepModuleStatsState.description: The functional state of this SEP. sepNotFound: SEP is not found. sepFound: SEP is found. sepDiagFailure: SEP dialog fail. sepNotOperational: SEP is not operational. sepLoading: SEP is loading data. sepInitializing: SEP is initializing. sepOperational: SEP is operational. sepDisabled: SEP is disabled.
